data.name: FiltrySadzySmokiJuniorOpis
data.value: Smoki Junior is a device that elimitantes up to 95% of soot particles created in wood-fired pizza ovens, reducing odors at the same time. The use of the Smoki Junior filtration system prevents the smoke ducts from becoming dirty and significantly reduces the risk of fire by cooling the smoke temperature. In installations where it is not possible to move out smoke by gravity, it is possible to equip the Smoki Junior with a fan that increase the natural draft. Smoki Junior is a practical solution wherever there are problems with too hot exhaust, odors and when fire safety requirements must be met.

data.name: FiltrySadzySmokiMaxiOpis
data.value: Smoki Maxi Grill is a device specially designed to filter soot and fats from exhaust air through the hood located above wood or charcoal grills. The Smoki Maxi Grill system eliminates up to 95% of soot and fat particles in the extracted air, while reducing odors and significantly lowering the temperature. The exhaust filter system Smoki Maxi Grill prevents contamination of the smoke ducts and significantly reduces the risk of fire by cooling the smoke temperature. Smoki Maxi Grill is a practical solution wherever there are problems with too hot exhaust, odors and in case when the requirements of fire safety must be met.

data.name: NawiewnikiWyporoweJRSOpis
data.value: JRS displacement diffusers are designed for low velocity air distribution. They have been adapted for ventilation of kitchens, where there are large heat gains. JRS displacement diffusers supply air to the occupied zone at a low speed. Inside there are deflectors that ensure even distribution of air over the entire surface of the perforated diffuser face. Recommended temperature of the air blown through the diffusers should be 3-6°C lower from the air temperature in the room. JRS diffusers are designed for ceiling mounting.

data.name: SystemAnsulR102SystemPrzeciwopozarowyOpis
data.value: The protection of catering equipment in professional kitchens with fire suppression systems allows to avoid serious consequences associated with fire outbreak. The ANSUL system protects human health and life, valuable equipments and rooms. The system reduces the hazard connected with inability to conduct business caused by the consequences of fire. Fire protection systems are taken into account by insurance companies which leads to lowering insurance costs.

data.name: SystemAnsulR102WymaganiaNaglowek
data.value: Requirements to be met by the contracting authority to ensure a guarantee of effective functioning.

data.name: SystemAnsulR102WymaganiaOpis1
data.value: When activated, the ANSUL R-102 system must cut off the power supply to devices under the hood (gas and electric). The control cabinet of the ANSUL R-102 system has NC contacts.

data.name: SystemAnsulR102WymaganiaOpis2
data.value: That is why a 3x1mm2 (max 3) wire/s should be brought near the box from gas valves and / or relays cutting off the power supply (valves and relays and wiring to the box out of Synergia responsibility). If it is necessary to connect to the alarm system in the building, connect another 3x1mm2 cable     (cable connection out of Synergia responsibility). When the ANSUL R-102 system is activated, the exhaust ventilation must remain switched on, while the supply ventilation should be stopped. Meeting the above requirements is a prerequisite for providing a guarantee of effective functioning of the ANSUL R-102 system.

data.name: WytyczneProjektoweSmokiJuniorOpis
data.value:
• SMOKI Junior duct connections should be treated like smoke ducts and stainless double-wall chimney systems should be used.
  • Due to the high humidity of the smoke leaving SMOKI and the very presence of smoke, the ducts must be tight and should be laid with a slope towards the device. If it is not possible to arrange the ducts with a slope towards SMOKI, install a fitting with the possibility of drainage in the lowest place of installation. The smoke duct shall be led above the roof in accordance with applicable chimney regulations.
  • DO NOT CONNECT SMOKI JUNIOR TO THE VENTILATION SYSTEM
  • Cold tap water should be connected to the SMOKI Junior device and permanently connected. The device automatically draws the right amount of water. A water filter is installed in the device.
  • A sanitary sewage system should be connected to the SMOKI Junior device. The drain should pass through the grease separator.
  • The SMOKI Junior device must be supplied with power supply and voltage compatible with the product card.
  • SMOKI Junior should be located as close as possible to the pizza oven, above the hearth. This ensures a short channel section exposed to soot deposition and high temperature. The device can be placed on the ground or attached to a wall or ceiling with a support frame.

data.name: WytyczneProjektoweSmokiMaxiOpis
data.value:
• SMOKI Maxi Grill duct connections between the grill and the device should be treated as smoke ducts and stainless double-wall chimney systems should be used.
  • It is recommended to make ducts for SMOKI Maxi Grill also in the chimney system, stainless ventilation fittings may be used.
  • Due to the high humidity of the smoke leaving SMOKI, the channels must be tight and should be laid with a slope towards the device. If it is not possible to arrange the ducts with a slope towards SMOKI, install a fitting with the possibility of drainage in the lowest place of installation. The exhaust channel should be led above the roof in accordance with applicable regulations.
  • SMOKI MAXI GRILL SHOULD NOT BE COMBINED WITH OTHER VENTILATION SYSTEMS
  • Cold tap water should be connected to the SMOKI Maxi Grill device and permanently connected. The device automatically draws the right amount of water. A water filter is installed in the device.
  • A sanitary sewage system should be connected to the SMOKI Maxi Grill device. The drain should pass through the grease separator.
  • The SMOKI Maxi Grill device must be supplied with power supply and voltage compatible with the product card.
  • The SMOKI Maxi Grill device should be located as close to the grill as possible, this ensures a short section of the channel exposed to orchard deposition and high temperature. The device can be placed on the ground or attached to a wall or ceiling.
